For more information about this process, please go to Appendix A - Check Out Asset Business Process to view the flowchart and process narrative. ## User Roles and Responsibilities The audience for this training includes the following user roles: | Role | Re

endix A - Check Out Asset Business Process to view the flowchart and process narrative. ## User Roles and Responsibilities The audience for this training includes the following user roles: | Role | Responsibility | |---------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------| | AssetAssigner | Assigns IT Assetsto and processesthe return of IT Assetsfrom Borrowers | ## Learning Objectives - · Describe how to assign and unassign Assets within Maximo - · Select Asset for check out - · Accept responsibility for Asset - · Recertify Asset - · Obtain Property Pass - · Acknowledge Asset receipt and unassign Asset - · View checked out Assets ## Agenda | Topic | Estimated Time | |---------------------------------------------|------------------| | Select Assetfor Check Out | 15 min | | Accept Responsibility for Asset | 10 min | | Recertify Asset | 10 min | | Obtain PropertyPass | 05 min | | Acknowledge AssetReceipt and Unassign Asset | 10 min | | ViewChecked out Asset

Assign Asset Borrower and Save ## ACCEPT RESPONSIBILITY FOR ASSET - ASSET BORROWER When you have been assigned an Asset(s), you will receive an email that includes a link to Maximo. Selecting the link for the asset will open the record in the Assets application. You will need to navigate to the Asset Acceptance application to accept responsibility for the asset. NOTE : If you are already working from the List tab of the Asset Acceptance application you can begin at Step 2.

to navigate to the Asset Acceptance application to accept responsibility for the asset. NOTE : If you are already working from the List tab of the Asset Acceptance application you can begin at Step 2. Step 10. From the Favorite Applications portlet, select Asset Acceptance . Figure 14. Open the Asset Acceptance Application - Sign Step 11. Place your cursor in the Asset Number field and press Enter to see the list of Assets assigned to you. Review the list and select the appropriate Asset(s) you are signing for. You may narrow the list results by entering information in one or more of the available filter fields Figure 15. Asset Acceptance - List Tab Step 12. Review the guidelines for VA Directive 6500 (via link), and then change the Assignment Status field entry from Assigned to Signed . The dates automatically populate. Figure 16. Assignment Status and Recertification Step 13. Select the Save icon on the toolbar to accept responsibility.

The dates automatically populate. Figure 16. Assignment Status and Recertification Step 13. Select the Save icon on the toolbar to accept responsibility. ## RECERTIFY ASSET - ASSET BORROWER You are required to recertify for Assets that have been assigned to you every 365 days. However, you can recertify at any time; you do not need to wait 365 days to recertify. A borrower designated as a contractor is required to recertify every 60 days. Email notifications containing a link to the Borrowers Asset will be sent as a reminder to recertify for assigned Assets. Employee Borrowers will receive their first notification email thirty days (30) prior to their recertification date. The user will also receive an email the day their asset is due for recertification. NOTE: If not recertified by the due date, borrowers will receive the following emails at 7, 14, and 21 days overdue: - · 7 Day Reminder Email : This is a reminder that you need to either

NOTE: If not recertified by the due date, borrowers will receive the following emails at 7, 14, and 21 days overdue: - · 7 Day Reminder Email : This is a reminder that you need to either sign or recertify for your Government Furnished Equipment (GFE) - · 14 Day Reminder Email: This is a reminder that failure to either sign or recertify for your Government Furnished Equipment (GFE) - · 21 Day Reminder Email: Due to a failure to sign or recertify for your Government Furnished Equipment (GFE), you are required to return the equipment immediately to your designated Office of Information Technology (OIT) service desk NOTE: Contractors will not receive overdue recertification emails if the person's Employee Type field is set to Contractor in the People application, on the Person record.
